          {
            "title": "Lesson #1",
            "id": 131692,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Environment variables store important settings, like passwords or access keys, outside of your code, making them easier and safer to manage.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #2",
            "id": 131702,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Environment variables in Python let you safely set key-value pairs for your code. This is very handy for storing sensitive information.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"import\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" os\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"api_key = os.getenv(\" /><text value=\"&quot;MY_API_KEY&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(api_key)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"11\" endIndex=\"18\" /><option startIndex=\"51\" endIndex=\"58\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"12345-abcde-67890-fghij-12345\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>api_key</code>, followed by <code>api_key</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #2 - Copy",
            "id": 131703,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Environment variables should always be securely stored to protect sensitive information.</p><p>You should never hardcode your API keys or passwords; the following example is for educational purposes to demonstrate their structure.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"environment_variables = {\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"&quot;API_KEY&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\": \" /><text value=\"&quot;12345-abcde-67890-fghij-12345&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\",\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"&quot;SECRET_KEY&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\": \" /><text value=\"&quot;mysecretkey&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"}\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(environment_variables)\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Don't do the above! It's dangerous to expose sensitive information directly in your code!&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /></content><output><content><text value=\"{'API_KEY': '12345-abcde-67890-fghij-12345', 'SECRET_KEY': 'mysecretkey'}\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"Don't do the above! It's dangerous to expose sensitive information directly in your code!\" /></content></output></code></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #2 - Copy - Copy",
            "id": 131704,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Instead of hardcoding sensitive information, we use environment variables set in the code execution environment but not hardcoded.</p><p>You can access a set in the environment via <code>os.getenv</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"import\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" os\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"api_key = os.getenv(\" /><text value=\"&quot;MY_API_KEY&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(api_key)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"21\" endIndex=\"23\" /><option startIndex=\"23\" endIndex=\"24\" /><option startIndex=\"24\" endIndex=\"30\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"12345-abcde-67890-fghij-12345\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>os</code>, followed by <code>.</code>, and finally <code>getenv</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
