            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>You can access environment variables by using <code>getenv</code> and specifying the key for the data you want to retrieve as the parameter.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"import\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" os\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"api_key = os.getenv(\" /><text value=\"&quot;MY_API_KEY&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(api_key)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"31\" endIndex=\"43\" /><option startIndex=\"21\" endIndex=\"23\" /><option startIndex=\"23\" endIndex=\"24\" /><option startIndex=\"24\" endIndex=\"30\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"12345-abcde-67890-fghij-12345\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>os</code> followed by <code>.</code> and then <code>getenv</code>, <code>\"MY_API_KEY\"</code>.</p></body></html>"
