          {
            "title": "Lesson #1",
            "id": 131708,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Traditionally, developers used <code>.env</code> files to store environment variables.</p><p>However, more modern development environments, such as Mimo, provide a more user-friendly way to set up environment variables.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #6",
            "id": 131697,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>The <code>.env</code> file is a text file that contains key-value pairs on separate lines.</p><p>API_KEY=12345-abcde-67890-fghij-12345<br />SECRET_KEY=mysecretkey.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #5",
            "id": 131696,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>If you save your environment variables in a <code>.env</code> file, you can use the <code>dotenv</code> library to load them into your environment.</p><p>Once loaded, you can access them using <code>os.getenv</code> in your code.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"import\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" dotenv\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"import\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" os\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"dotenv.load_dotenv()\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"api_key = os.getenv(\" /><text value=\"&quot;API_KEY&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(api_key)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"56\" endIndex=\"65\" /><option startIndex=\"66\" endIndex=\"75\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"12345-abcde-67890-fghij-12345\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>os.getenv</code>, followed by <code>\"API_KEY\"</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #7",
            "id": 131698,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>To read variables from a <code>.env</code> file in Python, we need to import <code>dotenv</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"import\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" dotenv\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"0\" endIndex=\"6\" /><option startIndex=\"7\" endIndex=\"13\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>import</code>, followed by <code>dotenv</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #8",
            "id": 131699,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>After importing the <code>dotenv</code> library, we can load the contents of the <code>.env</code> file using the <code>load_dotenv</code> method.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"import\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" dotenv\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"dotenv.load_dotenv()\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"15\" endIndex=\"21\" /><option startIndex=\"21\" endIndex=\"33\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>dotenv</code>, followed by <code>.load_dotenv</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #9",
            "id": 131700,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Once we've loaded the <code>.env</code> file with the <code>load_dotenv</code> method, we can access the variables in it with <code>os.getenv</code>.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"import\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" dotenv\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"import\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" os\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"dotenv.load_dotenv()\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"api_key = os.getenv(\" /><text value=\"&quot;API_KEY&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(api_key)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"46\" endIndex=\"53\" /><option startIndex=\"56\" endIndex=\"65\" /><option startIndex=\"66\" endIndex=\"75\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"12345-abcde-67890-fghij-12345\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>api_key</code>, followed by <code>os.getenv</code>, and finally <code>\"API_KEY\"</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #9 - Copy",
            "id": 132943,
            "contentType": "interactive",
