            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>What is the purpose of <code>load_dotenv</code> in a Python project?</p><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">It loads environment variables from a <code>.env</code> file into the environment</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">It creates a new <code>.env</code> file with default environment variables</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">It loads environment variables from a <code>.env</code> file into the environment.</p></body></html>"
