            "id": 131709,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>When working with environment variables in Python, there are multiple ways to load and access them, depending on your needs.</p><p>We already looked at <code>os.getenv</code>, now, we'll explore <code>os.environ</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #4 - Copy - Copy",
            "id": 131963,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>To access all environment variables, we use the <code>os.environ</code> dictionary. Every single environment variable is stored in this dictionary.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"import\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" os\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(os.environ)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"20\" endIndex=\"27\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"environ({\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  &quot;API_KEY&quot;: &quot;12345-abcde-67890-fghij-12345&quot;,\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  &quot;SECRET_KEY&quot;: &quot;mysecretkey&quot;\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  ...\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"})\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>environ</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #4 - Copy - Copy",
            "id": 131710,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>In modern systems, like Mimo, the environment variables are already set up.</p><p>However, if you use your own <code>.env</code> file, you have to load them first via the <code>load_dotenv</code> method.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"import\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" dotenv\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"import\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" os\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"dotenv.load_dotenv()\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(os.environ)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"0\" endIndex=\"13\" /><option startIndex=\"25\" endIndex=\"31\" /><option startIndex=\"32\" endIndex=\"43\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"environ({\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  &quot;API_KEY&quot;: &quot;12345-abcde-67890-fghij-12345&quot;,\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  &quot;SECRET_KEY&quot;: &quot;mysecretkey&quot;\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  ...\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"})\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>import dotenv</code>, followed by <code>dotenv</code>, and finally <code>load_dotenv</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
