            "id": 131711,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Just like with <code>os.getenv</code>, you can access a specific environment variable using the <code>os.environ</code> dictionary.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"import\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" os\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"api_key = os.environ[\" /><text value=\"&quot;API_KEY&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\"]\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(api_key)\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"21\" endIndex=\"31\" /><option startIndex=\"31\" endIndex=\"32\" /><option startIndex=\"32\" endIndex=\"41\" /><option startIndex=\"41\" endIndex=\"42\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"12345-abcde-67890-fghij-12345\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>os.environ</code> followed by <code>[</code> and then <code>\"API_KEY\"</code>, <code>]</code>.</p></body></html>"
